  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chuck all the broth ingredients into a blender and blitz until smooth. Season generously with salt and a bit more honey if needed – since it’s served ice-cold, the flavours will taste milder, so don’t be shy with seasoning."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the broth into an airtight container and stick it in the freezer for 30 mins to 2-3 hrs. The longer you leave it, the icier it gets. You can rake it with a fork to make savoury snow or let it semi-defrost before serving."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring a pot of water to the boil. Cook the noodles following pack instructions, then drain and rinse under cold water until completely cool."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Defrost the edamame in a bowl of cold water and drain off any excess water. Trim the cucumber and slice thinly using a knife or mandolin. Chuck it into a bowl with the edamame, kimchi, sesame seeds and vinegar. Season with a pinch of salt and toss to coat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When you’re ready to eat, spoon the icy broth into bowls, mix through the noodles and top with the cucumber salad."
    }
  ],
